"></a><div class=legend><a href=https://digital.library.cornell.edu/catalog/ss:19343476 target=_blank>Reynolds's Political Map of the United States, 1856</a></div></div><div><a href=http://hdl.handle.net/1813.001/8890000bk target=_blank><img class=image-media src=./images/PJM_1071_04_hu8a1e8085c7f4f56414f308a532bc5d01_473553_1200x0_resize_q75_box.jpg alt="Caetani, Cross Section of Hell, 1872"></a><div class=legend><a href=http://hdl.handle.net/1813.001/8890000bk target=_blank>Caetani, Cross Section of Hell, 1872</a></div></div></div></section></div></div><div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-3 col-lg-3 home-intro"><div class="region region-home-intro"><section id=block-block-5 class="block block-block clearfix"><h3>PERSUASIVE CARTOGRAPHY</h3><h4>The PJ Mode Collection</h4><p>This is a collection of “persuasive” cartography: ​more than 1200 ​maps whose primary intent or effect is to
influence opinions or beliefs - to send a message - rather than to communicate geographic
information. The collection reflects a variety of persuasive tools ​, including​ allegorical,
satirical and pictorial mapping; selective inclusion; unusual use of projections, color, graphics
and text; and intentional deception. Maps in the collection address a wide range of messages:
religious, political, military, commercial, moral and social.</p><p class=mt-3>Learn more about <a href=./about>persuasive cartography and the collection</a>.</p><div class=dropdown><button class="btn btn-default dropdown-toggle browse-collection" data-toggle=dropdown id=dropdownMenu1 type=button>BROWSE MAPS</button><p></p><ul aria-labelledby=dropdownMenu1 class=dropdown-menu role=menu><li><a href=./browse-date>Browse By Date Posted</a></li><li><a href=http://hdl.handle.net/1813.001/8890000zz target=_blank>Browse All</a></li></ul></div></section></div></div></section><footer><nav><div class="region region-footer"><section id=block-block-4 class="block block-block clearfix"><ul><li><a href=https://cornell.ca1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_ddqvYmIX7drYk5g>Feedback/Contact</a></li><li><a href=./content/references>References</a></li><li><a href=./credits-acknowledgments>Credits/Acknowledgments</a></li><li><a href=./copyright>Copyright/Use</a></li><li><a href=https://www.library.cornell.edu/web-accessibility>Web Accessibility Assistance</a></li></ul></section></div></nav></footer><script src=//stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/js/bootstrap.min.js integrity=sha384-ChfqqxuZUCnJSK3+MXmPNIyE6ZbWh2IMqE241rYiqJxyMiZ6OW/JmZQ5stwEULTy crossorigin=anonymous></script>
